      "timestep_posted": 42
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_13_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_13",
      "description": "Offering a mechanically sorted 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the S54 3.2L inline-six with individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS timing. This example utilizes a 6-speed manual gearbox delivering power through a factory M-variable limited-slip differential. The chassis has been enhanced with subframe reinforcement plates and the rod bearings have been addressed for long-term reliability. Suspension geometry is maintained by refreshed bushings and Bilstein dampers, ensuring the telepathic turn-in these cars are known for. While the exterior shows honest patina from spirited use, the powertrain remains robust with a linear power band and a 7,900 RPM redline. A superb driver\u2019s car for those who prioritize mechanical integrity and analog feedback.",
